                                    <br />Sri Sathya Sai Annapurna Scheme has target to provide nutritious meal to the needy and hungry  across various areas like the adivasi villages of Maharashtra , across various slums and hospitals as well. This Scheme comes under the umbrella of Sri Sathya Sai Trust, Maharashtra and will be implemented by the Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisation, Maharashtra.
                                    In the last year, around 1103 Narayan Seva activities have been performed which has benefitted around a lakh people.<br /><br />

                                </li>
